==English==
===Etymology===
{{F.}}, from {{L.}} ''[[fractio]]'', breaking, from ''[[frangere]]'', to break

===Pronunciation===
*frăkʹshən, /ˈfrækʃən/, /<tt>"fr{kS@n</tt>/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ækʃən|-ækʃən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# a part of a whole
#{{arithmetic}} a [[rational number]] written either as two [[integer]]s, one over the other and separated by a horizontal bar called a [[vinculum]], or side by side and separated by a [[slash]], or in [[decimal notation]] using a [[decimal point]].
# a comparatively small part
#:''a fraction of the cost''
#{{chemistry}} a [[component]] of a [[mixture]], separated by [[fractionation]]

